name: ethanol production from sugar beet molasses | ethanol, without water, in 95% solution state, from fermentation | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/3779/documentation

Inventory refers to the production of 1 kg hydrated ethanol 95% (dry basis, i.e. 1.05 kg hydrated ethanol 95% wet basis), respectively 1 kg of stillage syrup (wet basis) from molasses. The multioutput-process 'sugar beet molasses, in distillery' delivers the co-products 'ethanol, 95% in H2O, from sugar beet molasses, at distillery' and 'syrup, from sugar beet molasses, at distillery'.



This dataset includes the transport of molasses to the distillery, and the processing of molasses to hydrated ethanol (95%) and molasses stillage syrup (58% dry matter). System boundary is at the distillery. Dehydration to anhydrous ethanol is not included.
category: C:Manufacturing/20:Manufacture of chemicals and chemical products/201:Manufacture of basic chemicals, fertilizers and nitrogen compounds, plastics/2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Data from 1998 to 2005, current technology for the production of ethanol from sugar-based feedstocks
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data is from the etha+ project (Alcosuisse, CH)
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: The process is similar to that of sugarbeet-to-ethanol. The production of syrup from stillage includes pre-concentration and concentration. The syrup is 58% dry matter and is used as animal feed.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: none This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography CH. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Data is from the etha+ project (Alcosuisse, CH), technology by French ethanol plant supplier, modelling by ENERS (CH)
